                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Plenary Sessions/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName
                            corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-09T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 9, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 9—12:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. The comment on our speech has been favorable and in particular the members of
                    the Conference were gratified that we offered <pb facs="0151" n="31"
                        xml:id="pg_31"/> concrete and definite proposals which are very generally
                    felt to be a real contribution to the work of the Conference.</p>
                <p>Points Nos. 7 and 9 elicited the most attention and seem, in general, to have
                    been well understood.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
